<appendix id="jdm-xdm">
	<title>JSONiq Traversal Primitives</title>
	 <para>
		This appendix defines a set of primitives used to define traversal operations in JSONiq.
	</para>
	 <itemizedlist>
		<listitem>
			<para>
				<emphasis>j:pairs($object as object-node()) as pair-node()*</emphasis>
			</para>
			 <para>
				Returns the pair nodes that are children of the object <code>$object</code>.
			</para>

		</listitem>
		 <listitem>
			<para>
				<emphasis>j:name($pair as pair-node()) as xs:string</emphasis>
			</para>
			 <para>
				Returns the name of the pair node <code>$pair</code>.
			</para>

		</listitem>
		 <listitem>
			<para>
				<emphasis>j:value($pair as pair-node()) as node()</emphasis>
			</para>
			 <para>
				Returns the value of the pair node <code>$pair</code>.
			</para>

		</listitem>
		 <listitem>
			<para>
				<emphasis>j:members($array as array-node()) as node()*</emphasis>
			</para>
			 <para>
				Returns the members of the array node <code>$array</code>.
			</para>

		</listitem>

	</itemizedlist>

</appendix>

